---
themeColor: "#DD18B3"
tagline_short: "specialized skills for AI coding agents"
tagline: "Specialized agent skills that streamline common developer workflows and reduce token usage."
---
{% set example = skills[0] -%}
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en-US">
	<head>
    	<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">
		<meta charset="UTF-8">
		<meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge,chrome=1">
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, minimum-scale=1.0, initial-scale=1.0, user-scalable=yes">

		<meta name="theme-color" content="{{ themeColor }}">
		<meta name="color-scheme" content="light dark">

		<title>{{ title }} | {{ tagline_short }}</title>
		<meta name="description" content="{{ description }}"/>
		<meta name="keywords" content="{{ keywords }}"/>
		<meta name="author" content="{{ author }}"/>

		<meta name="robots" content="index, follow">
		<meta name="googlebot" content="index, follow">
		<meta name="bingbot" content="index, follow">
		<meta name="yandexbot" content="index, follow">

		<!-- Open Graph data -->
		<meta property="og:locale" content="en-US" />
		<meta property="og:title" content="{{ title }}">
		<meta property="og:url" content="{{ url }}">
		<meta property="og:description" content="{{ description }}">
		{# <meta property="og:image" content="{{ site.banner | imgSrc('png') | htmlBaseUrl(site.url) }}" /> #}
		<meta property="og:site_name" content="{{ title }}">
		<meta name="fediverse:creator" content="@castastrophe@front-end.social" />

		<link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" sizes="32×32">
		<link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml">
		<link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/favicon.svg">

		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
		<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
		<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Dancing+Script:wght@400..700&family=EB+Garamond:ital,wght@0,400..800;1,400..800&family=PT+Mono&family=Roboto:ital,wght@0,100..900;1,100..900&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

		<style>{% include "styles.css" %}</style>

		{# Load Font Awesome #}
		<script src="https://kit.fontawesome.com/42e99b4632.js" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
	</head>
	<body>
		<a class="skip-link" href="#main">Skip to content</a>

		<header>
			<h1>{{ title }}</h1>
			<p class="tagline">{{ tagline }}</p>
			<p class="badges" aria-label="Project badges">
				<a
					href="https://github.com/Allons-y-Studio/agent-skills/actions/workflows/test.yml"
					><img
						alt="CI status"
						src="https://github.com/Allons-y-Studio/agent-skills/actions/workflows/test.yml/badge.svg?branch=main"
				/></a>
				<a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@allons-y/agent-skills"
					><img
						alt="npm version"
						src="https://img.shields.io/npm/v/@allons-y/agent-skills?logo=npm"
				/></a>
				<a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/@allons-y/agent-skills"
					><img
						alt="npm downloads"
						src="https://img.shields.io/npm/dw/@allons-y/agent-skills?logo=npm"
				/></a>
				<img
					alt="Node 24+"
					src="https://img.shields.io/badge/node-%3E%3D24-brightgreen?logo=node.js"
				/>
				<img
					alt="License: MPL-2.0"
					src="https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MPL--2.0-blue.svg"
				/>
			</p>
			<p class="cta">
				<a class="btn btn-primary" href="#install">Get started</a>
				<a class="btn" href="https://github.com/Allons-y-Studio/agent-skills"
					>View on GitHub</a
				>
			</p>
		</header>

		<main id="main">
			<section id="what" aria-labelledby="what-heading">
				<h2 id="what-heading">
					What is this?
					<a class="anchor" href="#what" aria-label="Permalink to What is this?"
						>#</a
					>
				</h2>
				<p>
					<strong>Agent skills</strong> are bite-sized, self-contained capability
					packs you can drop into an AI coding agent. Each skill bundles a
					<code>SKILL.md</code> (the prompt and trigger description), a
					Node.js implementation, and a test suite — all under one directory.
				</p>
				<p>
					Claude Code installs them natively via the plugin marketplace. Other
					agent harnesses — Cursor, OpenCode, Aider, or anything built on the
					Claude Agent SDK — can vendor any skill directory with one
					<code>npx</code> command. No Claude-specific wiring.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section id="skills" aria-labelledby="skills-heading">
				<h2 id="skills-heading">
					Available skills
					<a class="anchor" href="#skills" aria-label="Permalink to Available skills"
						>#</a
					>
				</h2>
				<div class="skill-grid">
					{% for skill in skills -%}
					<article class="skill-card">
						<h3><a href="{{ skill.url }}">{{ skill.name }}</a></h3>
						<p>{{ skill.description }}
						</p>
						{% if skill.triggers.length > 0 -%}
						<p class="triggers">
							<strong>Triggers:</strong> {% for trigger in skill.triggers %}<code>"{{ trigger }}"</code>{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}
						</p>
						{%- endif %}
						{% if skill.commands.length > 0 -%}
						<p class="commands">
							<strong>Commands:</strong> {% for command in skill.commands %}<code>"{{ command }}"</code>{% if not loop.last %}, {% endif %}{% endfor %}
						</p>
						{%- endif %}
					</article>
					{%- endfor %}
				</div>
			</section>

			<section id="install" aria-labelledby="install-heading">
				<h2 id="install-heading">
					Install
					<a class="anchor" href="#install" aria-label="Permalink to Install">#</a>
				</h2>

				<div class="install-variant">
					<h3>Claude Code (recommended)</h3>
					<p>
						Register this repo as a marketplace, then install skills through the
						<code>/plugin</code> UI.
					</p>
					<pre><code>/plugin marketplace add {{ repo.name }}
/plugin install {{ example.name }}@{{ pkg_name | last }}</code></pre>
				</div>

				<div class="install-variant">
					<h3>Other agent harnesses</h3>
					<p>
						Use the <code>npx</code> installer to vendor any skill directory into
						your agent's skill folder. The installed payload is plain — just
						<code>SKILL.md</code> + scripts.
					</p>
					<ul>
						<li>
							<h4>List available skills</h4>
							<pre><code>npx {{ pkg_name }}</code></pre>
						</li>
						<li>
							<h4>Install a skill to the default location (~/.claude/skills/)</h4>
							<pre><code>npx {{ pkg_name }} {{ example.name }}</code></pre>
						</li>
						<li>
							<h4>Install to your agent's skill directory</h4>
							<pre><code>npx {{ pkg_name }} {{ example.name }} --dir ~/.config/cursor/skills</code></pre>
						</li>
						<li>
							<h4>Install everything</h4>
							<pre><code>npx {{ pkg_name }} --all</code></pre>
						</li>
					</ul>
					<p>
						For Node-runtime skills with dependencies, run
						<code>npm install</code> in the installed directory once vendored.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section id="programmatic" aria-labelledby="programmatic-heading">
				<h2 id="programmatic-heading">
					Programmatic usage
					<a
						class="anchor"
						href="#programmatic"
						aria-label="Permalink to Programmatic usage"
						>#</a
					>
				</h2>
				<p>
					Tool builders can enumerate skills dynamically via the exported
					<code>getSkills()</code> helper:
				</p>
				<pre><code>import { getSkills } from "{{ title }}";

const skills = getSkills();
// =>
// [
//   {
//     name: "{{ example.name }}",
//     path: "/path/to/skills/{{ example.name }}",
//     description: "{{ example.description | truncate(50) }}",
//     mdPath: "/path/to/skills/{{ example.name }}/SKILL.md",
//   },
//   ...
// ]</code></pre>
			</section>

			<section id="contributing" aria-labelledby="contributing-heading">
				<h2 id="contributing-heading">
					<a
						class="anchor"
						href="#contributing"
						aria-label="Permalink to Contributing"
						>#</a
					>
					Contributing
				</h2>
				<p>
					New skills, improvements, bug fixes, and documentation are all welcome.
					See
					<a
						href="{{ repo.url }}/blob/main/.github/CONTRIBUTING.md"
						>CONTRIBUTING.md</a
					>
					for environment setup, the test/lint/eval workflow, and the PR
					checklist.
				</p>
				<p>Some ideas if you're looking for a starting point:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>GitHub PR review summarizer</li>
					<li>Linear / Jira issue triage</li>
					<li>Slack digest summarizer</li>
					<li>Daily standup generator from git log</li>
					<li>
						Accessibility audit runner (pairs nicely with
						<code>design-system</code>)
					</li>
				</ul>
			</section>
		</main>

		<footer style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: .8rem; align-items: center; justify-content: center;">
			<div style="display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 1rem; align-items: start; justify-content: space-evenly;">
				<p>Licensed under <a href="{{ license.url }}">{{ license.name }}</a></p>
				<div style="display: inline-flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 2rem; align-items: start; justify-content: end;">
					<a href="{{ repo.url }}"><span class="fa-brands fa-github"></span> GitHub</a>
					<a href="{{ npm_url }}"><span class="fa-brands fa-npm"></span> npm</a>
				</div>
			</div>
			<p>
				Built and maintained by
				<a href="https://allons-y.studio"><span class="fa-solid fa-mug-hot"></span> Allons-y Studio</a> {{ divider | safe }} <a href="https://github.com/castastrophe"><span class="fa-solid fa-user"></span> Cassondra
				Roberts</a>.
			</p>
		</footer>
	</body>
</html>
